<section id="story" class="flex flex-col md:flex-row w-full">
  <!-- Left – founder portrait -->
  <div class="w-full md:w-55 relative overflow-hidden flex items-center" style="min-height: 360px; aspect-ratio: 3/4;">
    {%- if section.settings.founder_image != blank -%}
      <img
        src="{{ section.settings.founder_image | image_url: width: 1200 }}"
        alt="Gurkamal, Founder of BaseCode"
        width="848" height="1264" loading="lazy"
        class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full"
        style="object-fit: cover; object-position: top;">
    {%- else -%}
      <div class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #162a1e, #1C2E23);"></div>
    {%- endif -%}
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(28,46,35,0.80), transparent);"></div>
    <div class="relative px-10 md:px-20 py-20 mt-auto" style="z-index: 2;">
      <p class="font-mono-spec text-11 uppercase mb-6" style="color: rgba(196,120,58,0.60); letter-spacing: 0.2em;">
        03 — Founder
      </p>
      <p class="font-heading text-14 font-medium mb-2" style="color: rgba(245,242,236,0.50);">
        Gurkamal
      </p>
      <p class="font-heading text-13 font-light" style="color: rgba(245,242,236,0.35); line-height: 1.7;">
        Founder & Formulation Researcher · BaseCode Health
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Right – manifesto -->
  <div class="w-full md:w-45 px-8 md:px-20 py-16 md:py-20 reveal-hidden" style="background: #F5F2EC;">
    <p class="font-display italic mb-10" style="color: #1C2E23; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.3;">
      "I built the supplement I couldn't find anywhere."
    </p>

    <div class="font-heading text-16 md:text-17 font-light space-y-6" style="color: #4A5550; line-height: 1.9;">
      <p>
        My mom cooked every night. Not quickly, not conveniently. The kind of cooking that took hours
        — the fermented sour of fresh dahi sitting on the counter, lentils releasing that sweet nutty
        smell that meant dinner was almost ready, vegetables chopped from scratch for even the most
        ordinary Tuesday. Food was not fuel in our house. It was family. It was health. It was the
        whole thing.
      </p>
      <p>
        I didn't understand what I had until I left for university and slowly, without noticing,
        stopped having it.
      </p>
      <p>
        The supplements I tried didn't work. And when I started reading the research, I understood
        why. Most probiotic bacteria aren't engineered to survive stomach acid. The
        number on the bottle — 10 billion, 30 billion, 50 billion — is measured at manufacture,
        not at delivery. Without acid protection, you're paying for a number, not for results.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I found MAKTREK — a marine polysaccharide shield that actually protects bacteria
        through gastric transit — everything changed. Pair that with a prebiotic that feeds
        them on arrival, and you have something that actually works. Not a marketing claim.
        A delivery system.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then I read the HELIUS study — 2,084 people, 6 ethnic groups — and something clicked.
        Your heritage shapes your microbiome more than diet, age, or lifestyle combined. The problem
        isn't generic. It's ancestry-specific. The biological shift that hits diaspora communities isn't
        the same disruption everyone else faces. But every probiotic on the market is built as if
        it is. Seed built for Silicon Valley. I built for the world — one formula for every multicultural community, because the ancestral disruption pattern is universal.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am a wrestler and an avid lifter. I think about my body for a living. When my system is
        underperforming, I find out why. The science on this is published. The need exists. The
        population exists. Nobody built the ethnobiotic that solved both the ancestral disruption
        problem and the delivery problem. Until now.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="font-display italic mt-8 mb-8 pl-6" style="color: #C4783A; border-left: 3px solid #C4783A; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.4;">
      "I have a seven-month-old daughter. There are things I want to understand about my own biology before they become questions about hers."
    </p>

    <p class="font-display italic mt-10 mb-6" style="color: #C4783A; font-size: 18px;">
      "Your biology remembers.<br>
      That's why we built Origin."
    </p>

    <p class="font-mono-spec text-13 mb-8" style="color: #8A9490;">
      — Gurkamal, Founder · BaseCode
    </p>

    <a href="/pages/free-report" class="inline-block font-heading text-15 font-medium py-3 transition hover:underline" style="color: #C4783A;">
      Read the research that started it all →
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Founder",
  "class": "founder-section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "founder_image", "label": "Founder Photo" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
